		"body": "Fix: Handle Unicode Bidirectional Isolate characters correctly\r\n\r\nProblem\r\n\r\nJoplin incorrectly renders Unicode Bidirectional Isolate characters (U+2066–U+2069) as bullets, causing them to behave like neutral glyphs and breaking text direction/alignment.\r\n\r\nSolution\r\n\r\nPreserve these control characters instead of replacing them, allowing them to correctly influence text direction.\r\n\r\n Result\r\n\r\n No more bullet rendering\r\n Correct RTL/LTR behavior\r\n Proper alignment for mixed-direction text\r\n",
